      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(agents): cache provider tool schema normalization",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Cache provider-normalized tool schema `parameters` for repeated embedded agent turns, but only when OpenClaw can identify one of its bundled SDK tool-compat normalizers.\n- Keep the cache internal and conservative: bundled DeepSeek, Gemini, and OpenAI compatibility helpers can reuse cloned normalized `parameters`; custom provider `normalizeToolSchemas` hooks bypass the cache.\n- Avoid new public provider plugin contracts and avoid new operator-facing runtime flags. Tool objects, execute closures, approval state, guards, and runtime policy are still rebuilt per turn.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: repeated embedded agent turns can avoid redoing bundled provider tool-schema compatibility normalization when the provider/model/api/schema signature is unchanged. Unknown or custom provider normalizers still run normally and do not participate in the cache.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on macOS, branch `tool-schema-cache-pr3`, current PR head `dee9bc5aa9e603be72a640b3483ae669ade3c29e`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran a terminal proof with `node --import tsx --input-type=module` against the production `normalizeProviderToolSchemas` entry. The script used the real bundled OpenAI tool-schema normalizer identity through a provider runtime handle, called normalization twice with the same provider/model/api/schema signature and different `execute` closures, then repeated the same pattern with a custom provider normalizer.\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal output from the current head:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"head\": \"dee9bc5aa9e603be72a640b3483ae669ade3c29e\",\n  \"bundledCompat\": {\n    \"afterFirst\": { \"bypass\": 0, \"hit\": 0, \"miss\": 1, \"store\": 1, \"size\": 1 },\n    \"afterSecond\": { \"bypass\": 0, \"hit\": 1, \"miss\": 1, \"store\": 1, \"size\": 1 },\n    \"cacheHitIncreasedOnSecondNormalize\": true,\n    \"normalizedParametersEqual\": true,\n    \"secondRunExecuteClosurePreserved\": true\n  },\n  \"customProvider\": {\n    \"customNormalizeCalls\": 2,\n    \"afterCustom\": { \"bypass\": 2, \"hit\": 0, \"miss\": 0, \"store\": 0, \"size\": 0 },\n    \"customProviderBypassedCache\": true\n  }\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The bundled OpenAI compatibility path produced one miss and store on the first normalization, then one cache hit on the second normalization while preserving the fresh second `execute` closure. The custom provider path bypassed the cache twice and invoked its normalizer twice, proving the cache remains internal to known bundled compatibility helpers.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full live-provider latency and a remote LLM turn were not tested in this current-head refresh. This PR caches only provider-normalized schema `parameters`; it does not cache complete tool inventory/materialization, policy resolution, prompt inputs, or full agent-turn startup.\n\n## Additional validation\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/tool-schema-runtime.test.ts src/plugins/provider-runtime.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.test.ts src/agents/runtime-plan/build.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.runtime.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.runtime-errors.test.ts\n[test] passed 4 Vitest shards in 10.92s\nTest files: 6 passed\nTests: 124 passed\n\npnpm tsgo:core:test && pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check\nOK docs/.generated/plugin-sdk-api-baseline.sha256\n\npnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 <changed files>\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n\ngit diff --check upstream/main...HEAD && git diff --check\nexit 0\n```\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: Repeated embedded-agent turns reuse bundled provider tool-schema compatibility normalization for the same provider/model/api/schema signature, while non-bundled/custom provider normalizers still bypass the cache so plugin-specific behavior is not hidden.\n- Real environment tested: macOS local checkout at PR head `b183b3fbe3379f870b8a65e5bf2fe43c8e5aa2ca`; production `normalizeProviderToolSchemas` entry point; real bundled OpenAI normalizer `normalizeOpenAIToolSchemas` via runtime handle; separate custom runtime handle for the non-bundled provider path.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: Ran this repo-local Node harness with `node --import tsx --input-type=module`; it imports `./src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.ts` and `./src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/tool-schema-runtime.ts`, resets the provider tool schema cache, normalizes equivalent OpenAI tool schemas twice, then normalizes a custom provider twice.\n- Evidence after fix:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"head\": \"b183b3fbe3379f870b8a65e5bf2fe43c8e5aa2ca\",\n  \"bundledCompat\": {\n    \"afterFirst\": {\n      \"bypass\": 0,\n      \"hit\": 0,\n      \"miss\": 1,\n      \"store\": 1,\n      \"size\": 1\n    },\n    \"afterSecond\": {\n      \"bypass\": 0,\n      \"hit\": 1,\n      \"miss\": 1,\n      \"store\": 1,\n      \"size\": 1\n    },\n    \"cacheHitIncreasedOnSecondNormalize\": true,\n    \"normalizedParametersEqual\": true,\n    \"secondRunExecuteClosurePreserved\": true\n  },\n  \"customProvider\": {\n    \"customNormalizeCalls\": 2,\n    \"afterCustom\": {\n      \"bypass\": 2,\n      \"hit\": 0,\n      \"miss\": 0,\n      \"store\": 0,\n      \"size\": 0\n    },\n    \"customProviderBypassedCache\": true\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: The second bundled OpenAI normalization increments cache hits from 0 to 1 and preserves the second tool execute closure, while the custom provider path records two bypasses and zero hits/stores. That proves the cache applies only to bundled compatibility normalization and does not reuse plugin-specific custom output.\n- What was not tested: Live external provider latency or a paid remote LLM turn. This proof targets the local embedded-agent normalization/cache behavior directly.\n",
